# UMI3D reference repositories — read-only

The workspace may include several **UMI3D** trees as their **own roots** (multi-root). They are **upstream reference** for terminology, runtime behavior, and authoring tools. The **entire** tree under each root listed below is **read-only** in this workspace.

| Workspace folder (typical) | Upstream (informative) |
|-----------------------------|-------------------------|
| **`UMI3D-SDK-version-2.9`** | [UMI3D/UMI3D-SDK](https://github.com/UMI3D/UMI3D-SDK) |
| **`UMI3D-BROWSER-version-3.6_sdk2.9`** (Unity Browser) | [UMI3D/UMI3D-BROWSER](https://github.com/UMI3D/UMI3D-BROWSER) |
| **`UMI3D-Sketcher-no-history-2.11`** (Intraverse Sketcher / Sketcher) | [UMI3D/UMI3D-Sketcher](https://github.com/UMI3D/UMI3D-Sketcher) |

- **Do not** create, edit, delete, or refactor anything under those roots — including nested **`docs/`**, **`UMI3D-SDK/`**, **`UMI3D-BROWSER/`**, **`Intraverse/`**, dependencies, or any other path inside each root.
- They are **reference technology** that informs the **interactive-gltf** specification; portable definitions belong in **`proposals/`** and **`specifications/`** in **interactive-gltf-specs**; reference implementation code belongs in **`interactive-gltf-engine`** — not in these UMI3D trees.

If a change seems required in an UMI3D reference tree, **stop and ask the user** — local copies in the workspace must stay untouched.
